We can “build” the fixed‐assets section using only the items that “add” to fixed assets on the balance‐sheet. For example, in the sample the opening entry “Fixed Assets” of 5,000,000 and a fixed‐asset purchase of 305,354.43 were added (while the depreciation is recorded in an “accumulated depreciation” account and is reported separately). 

For the new problem the relevant rows are:

• An “Initial” entry with type “Fixed Assets” on 2023‑12‑31 with an amount of 5,000,000.00  
• A “Fixed Assets Purchase” row (id “FixedAsset20231231001”) on 2023‑12‑31 with an amount of 324,677.57

Thus the calculations are as follows:

 Fixed Assets Initial Value = 5,000,000.00  
 Fixed Assets End Value = 5,000,000.00 + 324,677.57 = 5,324,677.57

Below is the answer in the required json format.
